cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for mapping raw pixels from a camera to steering commands for self-driving cars. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques for processing visual data, as well as machine learning (ML) techniques for training the CNN. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG (machine learning) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of processing steps for better performance, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of neural networks for training and decision-making falls under neural networks (cs.NE).
